        <item>
            <title>1.4.0</title>
            <pubDate>2022-11-25</pubDate>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>12.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <enclosure url="https://github.com/chucker/Mastonaut/releases/download/app-1.4/Mastonaut-1.4.0.zip"
                sparkle:version="1.4.0" sparkle:shortVersionString="1.4.0" length="8102623"
                type="application/octet-stream" />-->
            <description>
                <![CDATA[
                    <div class="comment-body markdown-body js-preview-body" style="min-height: 509px;"><p>This is the first feature release since Mastodon went open source.</p>
                    <p><strong>Note:</strong> This release requires macOS 12.0 Monterey or newer. 1.3.10 is still available for macOS 10.15 Catalina and macOS 11.0 Big Sur.</p>
                    <h2>Features</h2>
                    <p><strong>Pull-to-refresh</strong>: You can pull from the top of a timeline column to refresh it.</p>
                    <p><strong>Always in Dark Mode</strong>: There's a new preference to make Mastonaut always show in <g-emoji class="g-emoji" alias="new_moon_with_face" fallback-src="https://github.githubassets.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f31a.png">ðŸŒš</g-emoji> <strong>Dark Mode</strong> or <g-emoji class="g-emoji" alias="sun_with_face" fallback-src="https://github.githubassets.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f31e.png">ðŸŒž</g-emoji> Light Mode. (By default, it uses whatever you have your system set to.)</p>
                    <p><strong>Lists</strong>: The columns popup now also shows any lists you've created, so you can browse those as well. (However, there is no support yet for managing your lists.)</p>
                    <h2>Fixes</h2>
                    <p>If a timeline was empty, a loading indicator would keep spinning in perpetuity.</p>
                    <h2>Contributors</h2>
                    <p><a class="user-mention notranslate" data-hovercard-type="user" data-hovercard-url="/users/uliwitness/hovercard" data-octo-click="hovercard-link-click" data-octo-dimensions="link_type:self" href="https://github.com/uliwitness">@uliwitness</a> and <a class="user-mention notranslate" data-hovercard-type="user" data-hovercard-url="/users/sbeitzel/hovercard" data-octo-click="hovercard-link-click" data-octo-dimensions="link_type:self" href="https://github.com/sbeitzel">@sbeitzel</a> made their first contributions in this release cycle. Thanks!</p></div>
                ]]>
            </description>
